51.9	Bergamot_orange	Bergamot orange	Citrus bergamia, the Bergamot orange, is a fragrant fruit the size of an orange, with a yellow colour similar to a lemon. Genetic research into the ancestral origins of extant citrus cultivars matched the bergamot as a likely hybrid of Citrus limetta and Citrus aurantium. Citrus bergamot is a native hybrid of and commercially grown in Calabria, southern Italy, where more than 80% are found. It is also grown in southern France and in CÃ´te d'Ivoire for the essential oil. The fruit is not grown for juice consumption.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cc/Citrus_bergamia_-_K%C3%B6hler%E2%80%93s_Medizinal-Pflanzen-184.jpg/220px-Citrus_bergamia_-_K%C3%B6hler%E2%80%93s_Medizinal-Pflanzen-184.jpg
